                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.79611 Pangborn-Herndon Flight/20:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Your 51, April 13. Department informed permission requested for Pangborn and
                    Herndon flight over Japanese territory as emergency measure. Should plane or
                    motor develop trouble pilots would attempt to reach Tokyo where service on motor
                    available. Proposed route as follows: Moscow–Novo
                    Sibirsk–Chita–Okhotsk–Nome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
